ADVENTURE WORK CYCLES KPI DASHBOARD

BUSINESS CASE
A global manufacturing company that produces cycling equipment and accessories needs a data-driven way to track key performance metrics (Sales, Revenue, Profit, Returns), compare performance across regions,, analyze product- and category-level trends, identify high-value customers.
Management wants a dashboard that integrates multiple data sources and provides real-time insights for strategic decision-making.

OBJECTIVES
-Connect & Transform Raw Data
-Build a Relational Data Model
-Create DAX Measures & Calculated Columns
-Design Interactive Power BI Dashboard

DATA SOURCE
Maven Analytics - 8 tables (sales, returns, products, product_categories, product_subcategories, customers, territory, calendar)

DATA MODEL OVERVIEW
Fact Tables: Sales, Returns
Dimension Tables: Customers, Products, Product Categories, Product Subcategories, Territory, Calendar
Relationships built using primary keys and foreign keys
Implemented standard snowflake-schema:
Fact → Dimensions → Dimensions → Measure Layer

KEY DAX MEASURES
Adjusted revenue, rolling profit, order target gap, YOY revenue %, average revenue per customer, etc.
(See full DAX syntax and calculations in the project_workbook)

DASHBOARD FEATURES
Executive KPI Summary: Revenue, Profit, Returns, Orders, Return Rate, Revenue Trend, Top 10 Products
Regional Sales Map: Compare territories across 3 continents - Europe, North America, and Pacific
Product-Level Analysis: Best-performing product lines and categories
Customer Insights: High-value customers, customer acquisition, and customer classifications
Interactive Controls: Slicers, Custom Navigation Buttons, Bookmarks, and more.

KEY INSIGHTS
Identified high-value customers who drive majority of revenue
Revealed regional disparities in profit and return rates
Highlighted top-performing categories to guide production planning

HOW TO USE
Download the project_workbook.pbix file
Open in Power BI Desktop
Ensure sample data paths are correct
View data model, measures, and dashboard
